Coconut Praline Toast
2 tbsp butter
1/4 cup firmly packed brown sugar
2 tbsp light cream
1/4 tsp vanilla
1/4 cup flake coconut
8 slice bread
Melt butter in saucepan. Remove from heat and add sugar, cream, vanilla, and coconut. Mix well. Let cool 5 mintues.
Remove crusts from bread slices. Toast slices on one side under broiler. Turn. 
Spread praline mixture to edge on untoasted side of each slice. 
Return to broiler and broil about 2 to 3 minutes, or until mixture is lightly browned. 
Cut each slice diagonally into thirds. Serve hot.
Make 24 pieces

Lemon Meringue Pie
1 package (3 5/8 oz) Jello Lemon Pudding and Pie Filling
1/2 cup sugar
2+1/4 cups water
2 egg yolks
1 baked 8-/9-inch pie shell, cooled
2 egg whites
4 tbsp sugar

Combine pie filling mix, 1/2 cup sugar, and 1/4 cup of water in sauce pan. Add egg yolk and blend well. Then add remaining 2 cups of water.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil and is thickened - about 5 mintues
Remove from heat. Coool 5 mintues, stirring once or twice. 
Pour into pie shell
Beat egg whites until foamy throughout. Add 4 tbsp sugar, 2 tbsp at a time, beating after each addition until sugar is blended. Then continue beatsing until meringue will stand in peaks.
Spread over pie filling. 
Bake in hot oven (425 F) for 5 to 10 minutes, or until meringue is delicately browned
